<Base
  title="How I Approach People: A Relationship Philosophy | Jevan Goldsmith"
  description="How Jevan Goldsmith thinks about friendships, partnerships, and the relationships that compound over a lifetime versus the ones that quietly drain you."
  canonical="https://jevangoldsmith.com/people-philosophy.html"
>
<header class="page-header">
        <div class="container">
            <h1>My People Philosophy</h1>
            <p>How I choose who to learn from, who to spend time with, and who shapes my thinking.</p>
        </div>
    </header>

    <main class="container">
        <article class="reading-philosophy-content">
            <section class="philosophy-section">
                <h2>Why People Matter</h2>
                <p>You become the average of the people you spend the most time with — in person, in books, in podcasts, and in your feed. I take that seriously. The people I follow shape the questions I ask and the standards I hold myself to.</p>
            </section>

            <section class="philosophy-section">
                <h2>How I Choose Who to Learn From</h2>
                <p>I look for people who have done the thing, not just talked about it. Track record over titles. Long-form thinking over hot takes. People who can change their mind in public and explain why.</p>
            </section>

            <section class="philosophy-section">
                <h2>What I Look For</h2>
                <p>Clarity of thought, honesty about tradeoffs, a long time horizon, and a sense of humor about themselves. I trust people who teach by showing their work and who treat ideas as tools, not identities.</p>
            </section>

            <section class="philosophy-section">
                <h2>How I Engage</h2>
                <p>I read their books, study their decisions, and steal their questions. I do not try to copy their lives. The goal is to borrow useful frames, not to become someone else.</p>
            </section>

            <section class="philosophy-section">
                <h2>Where to Go Next</h2>
                <p>Browse the people page to see who is currently shaping my thinking, then follow the threads from there into their books, essays, and interviews.</p>
                <p><a href="/people.html">Browse the people list</a></p>
            </section>

            <div class="back-to-books">
                <a href="/people.html" class="back-link">&larr; Back to People</a>
            </div>
        </article>
    </main>
</Base>
